longBusinessSummary: Varengold Bank AG provides various marketplace and transaction/commercial banking products and services to private and commercial customers in Germany, the United Kingdom, and Bulgaria. It offers call and fixed term deposits, and deposit guarantees; lending and fronting services; international payment transaction, trade and export finance, Lombard credit, and structured finance products; and payment, bank, delivery, and performance guarantees, and solutions for financing, as well as debt collection, forfeiting, and export financing services. The company was formerly known as Varengold Wertpapierhandelsbank AG and changed its name to Varengold Bank AG in July 2013. Varengold Bank AG was founded in 1995 and is headquartered in Hamburg, Germany.
